"<h3>Grilled Potato Wedges Recipe</h3>\n<hr>\n<ul>\n    <li>4 large potatoes</li>\n    <li>1/4 cup olive oil</li>\n    <li>2 teaspoons garlic powder</li>\n    <li>2 teaspoons paprika</li>\n    <li>1 teaspoon salt</li>\n    <li>1/2 teaspoon black pepper</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4>Instructions:</h4>\n<ol>\n    <li>Preheat your grill to medium-high heat (around 400Â°F).</li>\n    <li>Cut your potatoes into wedges of your preferred size.</li>\n    <li>In a small bowl, mix together the olive oil, garlic powder, paprika, salt, and black pepper.</li>\n    <li>Place the potato wedges into a large mixing bowl and pour over the olive oil mixture. Toss the potatoes to evenly coat them with the mixture.</li>\n    <li>Once the grill is heated, carefully place the potato wedges onto the grill grates. Be sure to place them so that each wedge has direct contact with the grates.</li>\n    <li>Grill the potato wedges for around 15-20 minutes, or until they are crispy and have grill marks on each side. Be sure to flip them occasionally to ensure even cooking.</li>\n    <li>Once the wedges are cooked to your desired level of crispiness, remove them from the grill and let them cool for a few minutes before serving.</li>\n    <li>Enjoy your delicious grilled potato wedges with your favorite dipping sauce.</li>\n</ol>"